* Initialization & Sourcing

This section ensures proper shell initialization across login and interactive shells.

** Shared Pre-Initialization

Code that runs before anything else, for both shells.
It checks first if it is running an interactive shell and if not, just quits
Then it adds the following directories to the PATH variable
    - ~/.bin :
    - ~/.local/bin
    - ~/Scripts: My personal Script folder where i store custom bits of code
    - ~/.screenlayout: Presonal folder that contains xrandr configurations to easily pass between different Monitor  setups
    - user/bin/python the location of the python binary as i develope quite a lot in Python

      the if  [-d "/directory/subdirectory] syntax makes ure to check that a folder exsists before it is added to the path 
      
#+name: shared-preface
#+begin_src bash
    # Generated from literate config: ~/dotfiles/shellrc.org
    # Do not edit directly - edit the .org file and retangle

    # Exit early if running non-interactively
    [[ $- == *i* ]] || return

  if [ -d "$HOME/.bin" ] ;
     then PATH="$HOME/.bin:$PATH"
   fi

   if [ -d "$HOME/.local/bin" ] ;
     then PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
   fi

   #add personal scripts folder to path
   if [ -d "$HOME/Scripts" ] ;
   	then PATH="$HOME/Scripts:$PATH"
   fi

   #add arandr scripts to path to switch monito setups
   if [ -d "$HOME/.screenlayout" ] ;
   	then PATH="$HOME/.screenlayout:$PATH"
   fi
   #add python to path
   PATH="/usr/bin/python:$PATH"
#+end_src

